WEBVTT

00:02.050 --> 00:03.709
<i>and change it forever.</i>

00:03.921 --> 00:04.999
That really spoke to me, man.

00:05.000 --> 00:06.905
I've had days like that,
when I couldn't breathe.

00:06.929 --> 00:08.339
<i>Make you feel like you belong.</i>

00:08.340 --> 00:10.289
Gina, I want a baby.

00:10.290 --> 00:11.629
I want a happy ending.

00:11.630 --> 00:12.796
So where do we go from here?

00:12.821 --> 00:14.185
<i>So when they do...</i>

00:14.210 --> 00:16.088
Why haven't you told
Maggie you were fired?

00:16.090 --> 00:17.459
My bosses weren't thrilled

00:17.460 --> 00:19.490
with how much time I took off this year.

00:19.515 --> 00:20.539
<i>... you hold on tight.</i>

00:20.564 --> 00:22.693
She applied for some
fellowship at Oxford.

00:22.718 --> 00:23.709
EDDIE: I am making the decision

00:23.710 --> 00:25.839
to be the best father
I can be for Charlie.

00:25.840 --> 00:27.339
That means being honest
with my children.

00:27.340 --> 00:28.789
I will not let you hurt my kids.

00:28.790 --> 00:29.790
I'm a good lawyer.

00:29.815 --> 00:31.565
You do not want to go up against me.

00:31.590 --> 00:33.490
- <i>Question is...</i>
- Jon left you money.

00:33.515 --> 00:34.629
- We don't want it.
- Mitch.

00:34.630 --> 00:36.049
I don't want my son finding out

00:36.050 --> 00:37.670
I've been lying to him his whole life.

00:37.695 --> 00:39.765
- <i>... what happens...</i>
- ROME: Jon is PJ's father.

00:39.790 --> 00:40.810
<i>... when you lose your grip?</i>

00:40.834 --> 00:43.167
The DNA test that was under
the bed, it's gone.

00:43.192 --> 00:44.839
PJ's Barbara Morgan's son?

00:44.840 --> 00:46.395
Why didn't you tell me?

00:47.903 --> 00:49.919
[THUNDER CRASHES]

00:49.920 --> 00:52.426
♪♪

00:52.451 --> 00:54.725
[GEARSHIFT CLICKS, ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

00:54.750 --> 00:57.958
♪♪

00:57.983 --> 01:00.528
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

01:01.514 --> 01:02.896
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

01:02.921 --> 01:04.129
[SIGHS]

01:04.129 --> 01:06.231
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

01:06.256 --> 01:08.614
Delilah, PJ is Jon's son.

01:08.952 --> 01:10.270
What? Jon's? No.

01:10.295 --> 01:12.218
- He is not.
- He is. He did a DNA test.

01:12.243 --> 01:13.570
It was a match.

01:16.281 --> 01:17.951
[WHIMPERS]

01:20.888 --> 01:23.146
Why do you think he
left her all that money?

01:23.171 --> 01:25.826
Because he felt guilty for
not being on that plane.

01:25.851 --> 01:27.561
Is that what he felt guilty for?

01:28.905 --> 01:30.927
[CRYING]

01:30.952 --> 01:32.670
Why did Jon make her that video?

01:33.386 --> 01:35.716
<i>JON: I'm sorry, Barbara.</i>

01:36.099 --> 01:39.638
<i>I left you just when you needed me most.</i>

01:39.663 --> 01:43.638
♪♪

01:43.663 --> 01:45.069
<i>FEMALE VOICE: Your
call has been forwarded</i>

01:45.093 --> 01:47.146
<i>to an automatic voice message system.</i>

01:47.171 --> 01:48.260
[BEEP]

01:48.285 --> 01:49.834
Hey, PJ.

01:49.859 --> 01:52.841
Uh, I didn't mean for you
to find out like that.

01:52.920 --> 01:55.724
I was planning to tell
you before my mom...

01:55.823 --> 01:58.388
Just call me back, please.

01:58.413 --> 02:03.576
♪♪

02:03.601 --> 02:05.850
No, Mikey, I don't know.
Barbara and I are worried.

02:05.875 --> 02:07.818
We haven't seen Patrick since yesterday.

02:08.449 --> 02:11.248
Yeah, I-I was supposed to pick him up,
and he didn't show.

02:11.473 --> 02:13.763
I-I don't know. 12 hours, maybe?

02:14.287 --> 02:17.123
Yeah, I don't know.
He stormed out of here upset.

02:17.148 --> 02:19.060
He's been in his own world,

02:19.085 --> 02:20.802
hanging out with a new group of...

02:23.837 --> 02:25.802
MITCH: Hey, pal, what are you doing?

02:25.827 --> 02:27.802
Is that the girlfriend
you were telling me about?

02:27.827 --> 02:29.482
PJ: Uh... yeah.

02:29.507 --> 02:30.597
Yeah, that's her.

02:34.018 --> 02:35.576
Hey, Mikey, when you stopped Patrick

02:35.601 --> 02:37.568
on his way to his girlfriend's house,

02:38.449 --> 02:39.982
where was that?

02:40.007 --> 02:44.388
♪♪

02:44.413 --> 02:46.685
- [KNOCK ON DOOR]
- Coming. I'm coming!

02:53.232 --> 02:54.709
Patrick.

02:55.348 --> 02:56.348
[SIGHS]

02:59.441 --> 03:01.021
I didn't know where else to go.

03:06.997 --> 03:11.880
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

03:14.785 --> 03:15.888
MAGGIE: Oh. Wow.

03:15.913 --> 03:18.123
I know you haven't heard
from Oxford yet, but...

03:18.148 --> 03:19.802
[LAUGHING] What is that?

03:19.827 --> 03:21.841
[BRITISH ACCENT] What,
this old thing? [LAUGHS]

03:22.459 --> 03:24.498
[IRISH ACCENT] I got it
for, uh, a sixpence

03:24.523 --> 03:26.279
when I bought you the wig.

03:26.304 --> 03:28.373
Your, uh, your British just went Irish.

03:28.398 --> 03:29.398
Really?

03:29.423 --> 03:31.084
Are you quite sure about that?

03:31.109 --> 03:32.920
Yeah, Bono, I am sure.

03:32.945 --> 03:34.474
[CLEARS THROAT]

03:34.499 --> 03:36.668
[BRITISH ACCENT] Please,
have a seat, m'lady.

03:36.693 --> 03:38.670
[IRISH ACCENT] Top o'
the breakfast to ya!

03:38.695 --> 03:41.380
This is very, very sweet.

03:41.405 --> 03:43.784
[COCKNEY ACCENT] I'm sure
you'll be gettin' great news

03:43.809 --> 03:45.568
- from good ol' Oxford
- [LAUGHS]

03:45.593 --> 03:47.998
in a queen's biscuit. [CLEARS THROAT]

03:48.023 --> 03:51.099
God, it's like I'm dating the chimney
sweep from "Mary Poppins."

03:51.124 --> 03:52.318
Forgot the marmalade.

03:52.343 --> 03:55.716
It's making all of my childhood
dreams very confusing.

03:55.741 --> 03:59.709
Or do they just suddenly make
sense, there, Mary?

03:59.928 --> 04:01.326
[LAUGHING] Are you okay?

04:01.351 --> 04:02.748
[NORMAL VOICE] Ah.

04:02.773 --> 04:03.880
I'm really not.

04:03.905 --> 04:06.295
[LAUGHS] That looked painful.

04:06.320 --> 04:08.216
There he is with the mayor.

04:09.574 --> 04:11.154
Is that... Is that Cam Neely?

04:11.179 --> 04:12.357
Yeah. Yeah.

04:12.382 --> 04:13.881
Jon knew everyone.

04:13.906 --> 04:18.005
♪♪

04:18.029 --> 04:21.192
You know,
there is something I want you to have.

04:21.475 --> 04:24.896
And full disclosure... It's broken.

04:24.921 --> 04:27.209
Jon was late to everything,

04:27.234 --> 04:30.177
and he used to say he
was wearing his excuse.

04:30.202 --> 04:31.310
"What do you mean I'm late?

04:31.335 --> 04:33.662
According to my watch,
it's 9:15 in the morning."

04:34.510 --> 04:35.799
It's a $20 watch.

04:35.824 --> 04:36.935
It never worked, no matter

04:36.960 --> 04:38.646
how many times he tried to get it fixed.

04:38.671 --> 04:40.170
But he loved it.

04:40.340 --> 04:41.998
It was his dad's.

04:44.184 --> 04:45.607
Are you sure?

04:45.632 --> 04:46.935
Yeah.

04:46.960 --> 04:49.326
You're... You're family now.

04:49.351 --> 04:50.459
You should have it.

04:50.507 --> 04:56.466
♪♪

04:56.491 --> 04:58.638
Why do you think he never
tried to reach out to me?

04:59.793 --> 05:02.076
I don't think he knew, PJ.

05:04.531 --> 05:06.326
There's a lot about Jon I didn't know,

05:06.351 --> 05:07.480
but he was a good dad,

05:07.481 --> 05:09.230
and he would've wanted to know his son.

05:09.231 --> 05:10.984
[VEHICLE APPROACHES]

05:12.293 --> 05:13.752
How did Rome know I was here?

05:13.777 --> 05:15.013
I texted him.

05:15.038 --> 05:18.060
He was... worried about you.

05:18.726 --> 05:21.065
PJ, I think you should
talk to your parents.

05:21.090 --> 05:23.888
- No, there's nothing...
- I know they lied to you, but...

05:25.053 --> 05:26.858
... maybe they had a good reason.

05:26.883 --> 05:27.922
[SIGHS]

05:27.947 --> 05:30.906
Or maybe they're the reason
he never got in touch with me.

05:30.941 --> 05:32.180
Maybe he tried

05:32.181 --> 05:33.640
and they stopped him.

05:33.641 --> 05:39.810
♪♪

05:39.811 --> 05:41.810
EDDIE: Thanks for meeting
me on such short notice.

05:41.811 --> 05:43.850
Your paralegal said you were swamped.

05:43.851 --> 05:45.086
Ah, no problem.

05:45.111 --> 05:47.484
And, hey, congratulations
on getting the house.

05:47.509 --> 05:49.773
[CHUCKLES] That is hard to pull off.

05:50.098 --> 05:51.881
Uh, usually, the wife gets it,

05:51.906 --> 05:53.266
especially when there's kids involved.

05:53.290 --> 05:55.247
I've heard stories about her in court,
but I don't need to tell you.

05:55.271 --> 05:56.810
You've seen firsthand
how horrible she c...

05:56.811 --> 05:58.060
Hey! Katherine!

05:58.061 --> 05:59.140
- Hey, Brian.
- Hi.

05:59.141 --> 06:00.187
How are you?

06:00.212 --> 06:02.128
I'm... good.

06:02.153 --> 06:03.383
Thank you.

06:04.552 --> 06:07.422
Um... I'm sorry.

06:07.447 --> 06:09.367
Didn't you ask me here about
custody stuff with your kid?

06:09.391 --> 06:10.391
Yes.

06:10.416 --> 06:11.654
Different kid.

06:11.679 --> 06:12.690
Oh.

06:12.717 --> 06:13.866
Different woman.

06:13.891 --> 06:15.000
Oh.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.060
You mean the woman that you...

06:18.061 --> 06:19.640
Ohh.

06:19.641 --> 06:22.586
PJ: You should've seen all
that stuff that Delilah had.

06:22.611 --> 06:24.740
All those memories...

06:25.311 --> 06:28.336
that I could've been a part of.

06:28.361 --> 06:30.687
H-How am I supposed to go in there

06:30.712 --> 06:32.656
and have a rational conversation

06:32.681 --> 06:36.203
with the people that lied
to me my whole life?!

06:36.681 --> 06:38.633
[SIGHS]

06:39.106 --> 06:40.726
Sounds like I'm going in with you.

06:40.751 --> 06:41.752
- [SEAT BELT CLICKS]
- No, no.

06:41.776 --> 06:44.047
- I-I need to do this myself.
- [SEAT BELT CLICKS]

06:44.072 --> 06:45.072
All right.

06:47.114 --> 06:48.609
I'll be right here.

06:51.734 --> 06:54.625
[EXHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS]

06:54.650 --> 07:01.650
♪♪

07:03.637 --> 07:05.097
Still can't find your passport?

07:05.122 --> 07:07.472
Oh, no, I did about half an hour ago.

07:07.497 --> 07:08.503
But I re-hid it

07:08.528 --> 07:10.722
because the feeling of
finding it was so gratifying.

07:10.747 --> 07:11.753
[LAUGHS]

07:11.778 --> 07:14.065
You know, if you just put
things back where they belong...

07:14.090 --> 07:15.534
You know, can we skip the TED talk

07:15.559 --> 07:17.715
about "a place for everything
and everything in its place"

07:17.739 --> 07:19.371
and just move on to the part
where you show me where...

07:19.395 --> 07:20.917
Boom!

07:20.942 --> 07:22.425
- Is that my passport?
- No.

07:22.450 --> 07:24.409
It's my passport,
and I know exactly where it is.

07:24.434 --> 07:25.987
Why is this so new?

07:26.012 --> 07:28.311
And why do you even have a passport

07:28.336 --> 07:29.519
if you haven't been anywhere?

07:29.544 --> 07:30.545
I don't need to go anywhere.

07:30.569 --> 07:32.184
I've got everything I
need right here in Boston.

07:32.208 --> 07:33.827
What about... Italy?

07:33.852 --> 07:36.183
- You love pizza.
- Do they have cheese in their crust?

07:36.208 --> 07:37.253
Next.

07:37.278 --> 07:38.737
[LAUGHS] All right.

07:38.762 --> 07:39.925
Um...

07:39.950 --> 07:41.761
You love "Crocodile Dundee."

07:41.786 --> 07:43.285
You ever thought about
going to Australia?

07:43.309 --> 07:45.503
Don't need to.
Paul Hogan brought it to me.

07:46.046 --> 07:48.120
[AUSTRALIAN ACCENT]
That's not a stapler.

07:50.028 --> 07:51.107
That's a stapler.

07:51.132 --> 07:52.206
[SCOFFS]

07:52.231 --> 07:55.020
Okay, but you could go hang
out with all those animals.

07:55.404 --> 07:56.519
How cute are kangaroos?

07:56.544 --> 07:57.545
[NORMAL VOICE] Super cute.

07:57.569 --> 07:59.019
But I don't trust them,
and neither should you.

07:59.043 --> 08:00.831
They box with their heads tilted back.

08:00.856 --> 08:01.910
How do they know to do that?

08:01.934 --> 08:03.224
Don't you have to go to work?

08:04.084 --> 08:06.855
'Course I do.
I'm an essential part of the machine.

08:06.880 --> 08:08.539
In fact, I'm gonna take this

08:08.564 --> 08:10.020
just in case I need
to leave the country.

08:10.044 --> 08:11.401
- Hmm.
- I'll be back tonight,

08:11.426 --> 08:13.052
and I suspect
you'll still be right here,

08:13.077 --> 08:14.981
- looking for your passport.
- Mm-hmm.

08:17.204 --> 08:18.520
Hilarious.

08:18.951 --> 08:20.130
Whoa.

08:20.155 --> 08:21.534
Hop.

08:21.559 --> 08:22.718
[CHUCKLES]

08:22.743 --> 08:23.912
All right.

08:23.937 --> 08:25.106
Bye, Roo.

08:25.131 --> 08:26.540
[AUSTRALIAN ACCENT] Bye, Dundee.

08:26.565 --> 08:28.484
[INHALES SHARPLY]

08:29.493 --> 08:30.702
[SIGHS]

08:30.727 --> 08:32.187
[DOOR CLOSES]

08:47.934 --> 08:49.434
Ohh!

08:51.911 --> 08:53.552
[SIGHS]

08:54.740 --> 08:56.779
PJ, where have you been?
We've been so worried about you.

08:56.803 --> 08:59.153
How could you do that?
How could you do that to me?

08:59.178 --> 09:01.059
Whoa, whoa. What are you talking about?

09:01.084 --> 09:04.442
Just stop it! Just for once,
tell me the truth.

09:04.945 --> 09:07.794
You are not my dad!

09:07.819 --> 09:11.895
♪♪

09:11.920 --> 09:14.411
Hey. Did PJ talk to his parents yet?

09:15.265 --> 09:17.059
He's still inside.

09:17.084 --> 09:19.325
And he was really, really upset.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.395
And I can't blame him.

09:20.420 --> 09:22.435
I mean, his... his folks kept
this huge secret from him

09:22.459 --> 09:23.653
his whole...

09:24.326 --> 09:25.872
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

09:25.897 --> 09:28.263
So it's okay if you and
Gina keep a huge secret

09:28.288 --> 09:29.998
but not if other people do?

09:31.289 --> 09:32.395
<i>D.</i>

09:32.420 --> 09:33.759
D, it's not like that.

09:33.784 --> 09:34.872
<i>Yeah. You're right.</i>

09:34.897 --> 09:37.497
And for the record, what's happening
with PJ is different.

09:38.617 --> 09:40.286
I have to go.

09:41.193 --> 09:42.523
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

09:44.757 --> 09:46.419
Please, just sit down.

09:46.444 --> 09:48.286
No, no, I'm not gonna sit down!

09:48.311 --> 09:49.690
Just tell me the truth.

09:49.715 --> 09:51.177
[SIGHS]

09:51.202 --> 09:52.849
All right.

09:55.499 --> 09:56.749
You're right.

09:58.575 --> 10:00.927
When I met your mom,
she was already pregnant.

10:01.245 --> 10:03.464
But she and I agreed
that I would raise you

10:03.489 --> 10:04.494
- as my son...
- My God. Just say it.

10:04.495 --> 10:06.872
Just say that Jon is my father.

10:07.203 --> 10:08.497
What?

10:08.530 --> 10:09.891
No.

10:10.370 --> 10:11.739
Patrick, you got it wrong.

10:11.764 --> 10:13.473
It's not Jon.

10:13.498 --> 10:15.427
Your mom had a boyfriend in college.

10:15.452 --> 10:17.081
They met sophomore year.

10:17.106 --> 10:19.052
- His name was David...
- Oh, my God.

10:19.315 --> 10:21.497
She lied to you, too.

10:21.522 --> 10:23.388
You don't even know, do you?

10:23.632 --> 10:25.184
What are you talking about?

10:27.034 --> 10:28.583
I did a DNA test.

10:28.608 --> 10:30.231
Jon is my father.

10:30.570 --> 10:31.661
- Didn't you...
- What?

10:31.686 --> 10:34.435
... ever wonder why he
left her that video?

10:34.460 --> 10:36.278
Why he left her all that money?

10:36.433 --> 10:37.482
Yeah, I know about the money.

10:37.506 --> 10:39.942
The money he left her because of me.

10:39.967 --> 10:41.700
No, she told me that...

10:41.980 --> 10:43.224
he left that money because

10:43.249 --> 10:44.826
- he felt guilty about...
- No, I get it now.

10:44.850 --> 10:48.280
The reason she didn't want me to know,

10:48.305 --> 10:50.599
is because she didn't want you to know.

10:51.712 --> 10:52.751
[SIGHS]

10:52.776 --> 10:54.395
♪♪

10:54.420 --> 10:56.419
[DOOR OPENS]

10:56.908 --> 10:58.231
[DOOR CLOSES]

10:58.256 --> 11:00.395
♪♪

11:00.420 --> 11:03.263
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

11:03.288 --> 11:05.700
♪♪

11:05.725 --> 11:07.014
Come on. Let's go.

11:07.039 --> 11:08.079
What happened? Are you okay?

11:08.103 --> 11:09.177
No.

11:09.202 --> 11:10.786
M-Maybe we should go back inside...

11:10.811 --> 11:12.802
Please. Just drive.

11:15.518 --> 11:16.768
Please.

11:19.815 --> 11:21.325
Gary.

11:22.144 --> 11:23.911
It's been three days.

11:24.207 --> 11:26.575
You have to tell Maggie you were fired.

11:28.308 --> 11:30.427
Be careful what you push for, Enid.

11:30.452 --> 11:32.395
Your house has never looked better.

11:32.420 --> 11:35.059
Come on, what... what are we doing here?

11:35.084 --> 11:36.849
No! [CHUCKLES]

11:36.874 --> 11:39.505
Bennett was the same way...
Very particular.

11:39.530 --> 11:40.856
I can't tell you how many times

11:40.881 --> 11:42.341
we had to drive back to the house

11:42.366 --> 11:44.583
to make sure that the
garage door was closed.

11:44.608 --> 11:46.669
- It's good to check.
- [CHUCKLES]

11:46.694 --> 11:49.863
He would do this thing where
the volume on the car radio

11:49.888 --> 11:52.614
always had to be set to an
even number... never odd.

11:52.639 --> 11:54.308
Do you do that, too?

11:54.333 --> 11:56.130
I do now. [SIGHS]

11:56.155 --> 11:57.904
[BOTH LAUGH]

11:57.929 --> 11:59.700
Sorry. [LAUGHS]

12:00.099 --> 12:02.583
- Ohh...
- Yeah, I guess, uh...

12:02.744 --> 12:05.073
I've kind of become a creature of habit.

12:05.106 --> 12:07.833
I've been told, uh,
I'm not good with change,

12:07.858 --> 12:10.541
which is unfortunate, because lately,

12:10.566 --> 12:12.333
it seems like everything's changing.

12:14.149 --> 12:15.609
[WESLEY WHINES]

12:18.603 --> 12:20.450
- What's with you?
- Nothing.

12:20.475 --> 12:22.231
I'm just...

12:22.432 --> 12:24.325
I'm so happy you got your dog back.

12:24.350 --> 12:26.599
It was very sweet of you to find Wesley.

12:26.624 --> 12:28.489
- Oh.
- I really appreciate it.

12:28.514 --> 12:29.950
I'm just a man.

12:30.838 --> 12:33.708
And I didn't want
to say this to you, but...

12:34.865 --> 12:36.622
... he's not my dog.

12:36.870 --> 12:38.079
What?

12:38.104 --> 12:39.786
- He isn't.
- No!

12:39.811 --> 12:41.263
No. Enid, come on.

12:41.288 --> 12:42.947
Come on. I think it is.

12:42.972 --> 12:45.317
Look at this big ol' face!

12:45.342 --> 12:48.481
This is definitely, definitely a Wesley.

12:48.506 --> 12:50.888
[LAUGHS] What's wrong with you, huh?

12:50.913 --> 12:52.638
How could you run away from Enid?

12:52.663 --> 12:54.216
Gary.

12:54.533 --> 12:56.403
This isn't Wesley.

12:57.539 --> 13:00.578
But you know what?
I love him just as much.

13:00.735 --> 13:03.419
Sometimes, change can be good.

13:05.112 --> 13:07.571
Right now, I should let you know that,

13:07.596 --> 13:11.177
legally, financially,
you are on the hook

13:11.202 --> 13:13.371
for nothing.

13:13.396 --> 13:14.536
Nada.

13:14.561 --> 13:16.856
So, before you go and give away

13:16.881 --> 13:19.434
what could be a small
cottage in Nantucket,

13:19.459 --> 13:22.038
I should let you know
that I pay a lot of money

13:22.063 --> 13:24.380
for a kid that I see two
months during the summer.

13:24.405 --> 13:25.716
Brian...

13:25.930 --> 13:27.333
Right.

13:27.946 --> 13:29.755
Well, listen, as your attorney...

13:29.780 --> 13:31.325
Who's paid by the hour...

13:31.350 --> 13:33.294
I'm very happy to go
over your legal options,

13:33.319 --> 13:36.747
but a-are you sure that there's no way

13:36.772 --> 13:38.326
to resolve this without going to court?

13:38.350 --> 13:39.939
I've tried talking to Delilah.

13:39.964 --> 13:41.373
Katherine's tried talking to her.

13:41.398 --> 13:43.239
She just doesn't see it our way.

13:43.264 --> 13:45.093
Right.

13:45.118 --> 13:48.099
But, counselor, with all due respect,

13:48.124 --> 13:51.003
this isn't about two
companies going at it.

13:51.028 --> 13:52.411
These are people.

13:52.805 --> 13:55.764
And you should know,
once you go down this road,

13:55.882 --> 13:57.461
it could get very ugly.

14:00.236 --> 14:05.525
♪♪

14:05.550 --> 14:08.286
[PANTING]

14:15.383 --> 14:17.200
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

14:17.225 --> 14:18.434
GARY: Maggie!

14:18.459 --> 14:20.178
- MAGGIE: I don't think I can do this.
- It's okay.

14:20.202 --> 14:21.669
It's okay.

14:22.247 --> 14:23.825
- I'm in.
- You're in.

14:23.850 --> 14:25.388
I love you, Gary Mendez.

14:25.413 --> 14:28.076
TOGETHER: Three, two, one!

14:28.101 --> 14:30.489
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

14:30.514 --> 14:37.514
♪♪

14:47.563 --> 14:49.564
I made us a little something to drink.

14:49.589 --> 14:51.189
Family recipe.

14:53.814 --> 14:55.063
Whoa!

14:55.064 --> 14:57.199
- Is this lemonade?
- Mostly.

14:57.224 --> 14:58.916
- Heh ha!
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

14:59.490 --> 15:01.101
Uh, excuse me.

15:01.126 --> 15:02.625
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]
- Ed.

15:02.650 --> 15:04.146
Uh, did I catch you at a bad time?

15:04.171 --> 15:06.724
Just unintentionally day-drinking.
What's up?

15:06.749 --> 15:08.256
Just this paternity stuff.

15:08.281 --> 15:09.888
Delilah and I aren't seeing eye-to-eye,

15:09.913 --> 15:12.537
and Katherine and I were
hoping you could talk to her

15:12.562 --> 15:14.201
before we have to get lawyers involved.

15:14.226 --> 15:15.342
Lawyers?

15:15.367 --> 15:16.599
I don't know what else to do.

15:16.624 --> 15:20.646
<i>If Delilah isn't willing to
sign the forms voluntarily,</i>

15:20.671 --> 15:22.640
then, legally...

15:22.963 --> 15:24.631
we have to get a blood
sample from Charlie

15:24.656 --> 15:26.025
to prove that I'm the father.

15:26.050 --> 15:28.179
That seems a bit
extreme, don't you think?

15:28.204 --> 15:29.823
<i>I know.</i>

15:29.848 --> 15:32.084
But that's why we want
you to talk to her.

15:32.691 --> 15:34.571
She listens to you.
You're like a brother to her.

15:34.595 --> 15:36.552
Oh, am I? Because
I don't have sex with her?

15:36.577 --> 15:37.843
Is that how we found that dynamic?

15:37.867 --> 15:40.435
Dude, this is why you do not...

15:40.778 --> 15:43.349
crap where you eat.

15:43.746 --> 15:45.210
You know how hard it's
been for all of us

15:45.234 --> 15:46.654
to navigate what you two did?

15:46.679 --> 15:48.357
<i>And now, what, you're asking me</i>

15:48.382 --> 15:50.622
<i>to choose between my best friends?</i>

15:52.048 --> 15:53.576
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:53.852 --> 15:56.412
Hey. I got your text. Is Patrick okay?

15:56.437 --> 15:57.727
Patrick?

15:59.318 --> 16:01.157
- Where is he?
- Gone.

16:01.182 --> 16:02.477
What do you mean "gone"?

16:02.502 --> 16:03.712
He left.

16:05.376 --> 16:07.508
All these years,
you've been lying to me.

16:07.533 --> 16:09.452
What... What are you talking about?

16:09.477 --> 16:11.186
I'm done falling for it, Barbara.

16:11.211 --> 16:12.782
I know.

16:12.807 --> 16:14.235
Patrick is Jon's son.

16:14.260 --> 16:15.711
He told me everything.

16:15.736 --> 16:17.075
W-What?

16:17.100 --> 16:18.782
He was right. I am such an idiot.

16:18.807 --> 16:20.096
You're lying to me right now.

16:20.121 --> 16:22.170
He did a DNA test.

16:22.195 --> 16:23.695
It's all right here.

16:26.286 --> 16:28.665
This says that PJ's DNA matches...

16:28.815 --> 16:31.891
Wh... Hai... Hairs found...
Found on what... what sweater?

16:34.635 --> 16:35.938
This one.

16:37.075 --> 16:38.664
Oh, my God.

16:38.689 --> 16:45.368
♪♪

16:45.966 --> 16:47.875
It is so nice up here.

16:47.900 --> 16:50.204
You ever, uh... You ever barbecue?

16:50.576 --> 16:51.899
Sometimes.

16:52.722 --> 16:55.680
I gotta say, you're taking this a
lot better than I thought you would.

16:55.705 --> 16:57.547
Yeah, actually, this is...

16:57.572 --> 16:59.547
This is the best I've
felt in a long time.

16:59.572 --> 17:01.422
The truth is finally out.

17:01.447 --> 17:02.868
I know who I am.

17:04.713 --> 17:05.977
Okay, then.

17:06.607 --> 17:08.070
I guess I'm happy for you.

17:08.096 --> 17:09.359
Yeah, me too.

17:10.003 --> 17:12.633
And as hard as it is to
not have known Jon...

17:13.398 --> 17:15.883
I mean, I'm... I'm family now.

17:22.955 --> 17:25.532
Hey, D, uh, call me.

17:25.558 --> 17:27.595
I just want to make sure you're okay.

17:28.549 --> 17:31.416
- Um, I know it was a lot of...
- MAGGIE: Gina?

17:31.441 --> 17:32.986
Um, just call me.

17:33.011 --> 17:35.236
Maggie, what are you doing here?
Is everything okay?

17:35.261 --> 17:37.300
- I needed to talk to you.
- Okay.

17:37.325 --> 17:39.002
- Maybe... I shouldn't.
- Okay.

17:39.027 --> 17:40.517
- No, I need to.
- Okay.

17:40.542 --> 17:42.845
Uh, has Gary mentioned anything to you?

17:43.880 --> 17:47.674
I'm... gonna need a
little more information.

17:47.699 --> 17:48.775
Um...

17:48.800 --> 17:50.330
Has he...

17:50.355 --> 17:53.424
told you a big piece of news

17:53.449 --> 17:56.830
that I haven't found out about yet?

17:57.020 --> 17:58.603
He has.

17:59.191 --> 18:01.267
And I promised I wouldn't say anything.

18:01.292 --> 18:02.791
[INHALES SHARPLY]

18:02.816 --> 18:03.985
So maybe you say something?

18:04.010 --> 18:05.103
I found the ring.

18:05.128 --> 18:06.246
Oh.

18:06.271 --> 18:07.588
Oh!

18:07.855 --> 18:10.377
Yes. The ring.

18:10.402 --> 18:12.338
Yeah, don't get me wrong...
It's beautiful.

18:12.363 --> 18:14.228
I mean, I don't know if
you helped pick it out,

18:14.253 --> 18:15.478
but it is beautiful.

18:15.503 --> 18:18.728
But it's just such a weird
time to be doing that.

18:18.753 --> 18:21.361
I mean, I might be going
to Oxford for a year,

18:21.386 --> 18:23.213
and he said he could come with me,

18:23.238 --> 18:25.572
but his job, his life.

18:25.597 --> 18:29.150
How can he just leave
everything behind for me?

18:29.175 --> 18:30.214
[DOOR CLOSES]

18:30.239 --> 18:31.578
I...

18:31.603 --> 18:32.994
Delilah, there you are.

18:33.019 --> 18:34.252
Did you get my message?

18:34.277 --> 18:35.894
Hi, Maggie.

18:35.919 --> 18:37.144
Hey.

18:37.263 --> 18:38.761
Is everything okay?

18:40.010 --> 18:41.010
I don't know.

18:41.035 --> 18:43.370
Gary texted me saying he
wanted to meet me here

18:43.395 --> 18:45.331
with Katherine and Eddie.

18:45.356 --> 18:47.433
Wait, Gary's coming here?

18:47.458 --> 18:48.472
Yeah.

18:48.497 --> 18:51.956
Seems like a lot of people are
talking about me behind my back.

18:52.448 --> 18:56.613
♪♪

18:56.638 --> 18:58.120
I'm gonna...

18:58.145 --> 19:00.534
I'm gonna give you guys a... second.

19:00.559 --> 19:02.652
Oop! Turn around. Trust me, turn around.

19:04.048 --> 19:06.048
You know, when you asked me
to help move all this stuff,

19:06.072 --> 19:08.652
I kind of imagined us doing it together.

19:11.187 --> 19:13.605
- What are they doing here?
- I don't know.

19:13.756 --> 19:16.558
They were waiting by the
door when I came downstairs.

19:16.583 --> 19:17.870
MITCH: Patrick, please.

19:17.895 --> 19:20.159
We're here 'cause we need
to tell you the truth.

19:21.668 --> 19:23.488
I didn't tell you about PJ

19:23.513 --> 19:26.081
because I was looking out for you.

19:26.106 --> 19:28.515
I was waiting to know for
sure that it was true.

19:28.540 --> 19:30.191
Well, knowing whether it was true or not

19:30.216 --> 19:32.815
didn't seem to stop you from
keeping information from me

19:32.840 --> 19:34.386
about my life!

19:35.493 --> 19:39.636
No, I-I'm telling you,
PJ, Dave is your father.

19:40.801 --> 19:42.230
He and Jon were best friends.

19:42.255 --> 19:43.824
No, the DNA test.

19:43.849 --> 19:45.581
Jon is my father. I tested the sweater.

19:45.606 --> 19:47.275
No, honey.

19:47.300 --> 19:48.433
[SIGHS]

19:48.458 --> 19:50.589
When Dave died,
that sweater was the only thing

19:50.614 --> 19:52.283
of your father's that Jon wanted.

19:52.308 --> 19:58.112
♪♪

19:58.137 --> 20:00.355
No. No, I...

20:00.380 --> 20:01.380
Baby, sit down.

20:01.405 --> 20:03.271
- Let me explain this to you.
- No, no. I don't want to hear it.

20:03.295 --> 20:04.903
- Please!
- Hey. Patrick!

20:04.928 --> 20:06.597
I said I don't want to hear it.

20:06.622 --> 20:08.022
- [DOOR OPENS]
- Let me talk to him.

20:08.322 --> 20:09.571
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:18.324 --> 20:19.744
Thank you.

20:23.297 --> 20:25.238
GARY: Can I buy you a drink?

20:26.111 --> 20:27.715
Hey.

20:27.938 --> 20:29.316
What is that look?

20:29.341 --> 20:31.410
- Um, uh...
- What are you doing here?

20:31.435 --> 20:33.363
Uh, Regina and I were just discussing...

20:33.388 --> 20:34.941
Gary, hey.

20:34.966 --> 20:36.113
How'd it go with D?

20:36.138 --> 20:38.027
Is she willing to correct
the birth certificate?

20:38.052 --> 20:39.052
MAGGIE: What?

20:39.077 --> 20:40.684
I haven't talked to her yet.

20:41.338 --> 20:43.574
Well, then, what are we doing here?

20:43.599 --> 20:45.512
You asked me to fix this, Ed.

20:45.537 --> 20:47.386
- This is me fixing it.
- DELILAH: Stop telling me what to do!

20:47.410 --> 20:50.049
I'm not trying to tell
you what to do, D.

20:50.074 --> 20:51.902
- I'm trying to help!
- Well, you're not helping.

20:51.926 --> 20:54.463
This is my family!
It... It doesn't involve you.

20:54.488 --> 20:55.916
Maybe it should involve her.

20:55.941 --> 20:58.354
Of course you think that.
She's on your side.

20:58.379 --> 21:00.752
Oh, D, I'm not taking sides.

21:00.777 --> 21:02.526
- [SCOFFS]
- The fact is,

21:02.551 --> 21:05.291
you had the affair,
you kept this a secret,

21:05.316 --> 21:08.276
and now you are angry at anyone
who doesn't share your opinion.

21:08.301 --> 21:10.066
- All right, everybody, stop talking.
- You know, Gina?

21:10.090 --> 21:12.830
I get that you think you know what's
best, but you don't have kids.

21:12.855 --> 21:14.823
So how can you possibly
know what's best for mine?

21:14.848 --> 21:16.346
Stop! Just stop!

21:16.371 --> 21:19.416
You three need to talk.

21:19.441 --> 21:20.494
We've tried.

21:20.519 --> 21:21.940
Well, try harder.

21:21.965 --> 21:24.698
I cannot believe that it's come to this.

21:25.174 --> 21:26.972
You're really gonna take
legal action? Come on.

21:26.996 --> 21:28.424
Legal... W-What?!

21:28.449 --> 21:30.213
Yeah. That's right, D.

21:30.238 --> 21:31.534
They want you to sign a form

21:31.559 --> 21:33.160
that proves that Eddie
is Charlie's father.

21:33.184 --> 21:35.096
I-I can't believe you would do that.

21:35.121 --> 21:37.666
I can't believe any of
you would do any of this!

21:37.691 --> 21:39.270
You're better than that.

21:39.401 --> 21:40.494
Least, I thought you were.

21:40.519 --> 21:42.354
- We just want...
- I know, Ed. I know.

21:42.379 --> 21:43.901
You want what's best for Charlie.

21:43.926 --> 21:45.425
Everyone wants what's
best for their family.

21:45.449 --> 21:47.994
Well, what about this family?

21:48.019 --> 21:49.182
My family.

21:49.207 --> 21:51.635
Because what you're doing
is ripping us apart.

21:52.636 --> 21:55.425
Ever since Jon died, I am trying.

21:55.426 --> 21:57.268
I'm trying to keep us together.

21:58.056 --> 21:59.940
Man, I took you in.

22:01.306 --> 22:03.462
I agreed to be the guardian of your kid.

22:03.487 --> 22:08.643
♪♪

22:08.668 --> 22:10.041
And, D...

22:10.066 --> 22:12.354
I held you in that driveway.

22:12.379 --> 22:14.361
I told you he was gone.

22:14.386 --> 22:15.808
And I promised that I would be there

22:15.832 --> 22:17.877
and that we would still be a family.

22:17.902 --> 22:19.752
I have stood by you through everything,

22:19.777 --> 22:21.058
even when I didn't agree with you,

22:21.082 --> 22:23.909
because you are like a sister to me.

22:25.086 --> 22:28.791
I've spent so much time
helping people through cancer

22:28.816 --> 22:32.010
and depression and divorce

22:32.868 --> 22:36.252
that... here's an
interesting little fact.

22:36.559 --> 22:38.284
I lost my job!

22:39.396 --> 22:41.377
But I would do it all over again

22:41.402 --> 22:44.182
if it meant keeping us together.

22:44.733 --> 22:46.877
Because I can get another job.

22:48.775 --> 22:53.604
But I cannot get... another family!

22:54.901 --> 22:56.127
Look where we're standing.

22:56.152 --> 22:59.323
This... This was Jon's last gift to us.

22:59.871 --> 23:02.682
You think this is the
someday he imagined?

23:03.005 --> 23:04.674
It's not!

23:04.699 --> 23:06.705
And it's not the one I imagined, either!

23:07.744 --> 23:09.463
So clean it up!

23:09.488 --> 23:16.488
♪♪

23:17.456 --> 23:20.807
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

23:25.829 --> 23:26.924
[DOOR CLOSES]

23:26.949 --> 23:28.737
Hey.

23:28.762 --> 23:30.604
I know it's a lot, man.

23:30.629 --> 23:32.424
No, you don't know. [INHALES SHARPLY]

23:32.449 --> 23:33.784
You don't get it.

23:34.121 --> 23:37.369
For so long, it didn't make sense.

23:37.394 --> 23:40.877
It just didn't feel like
Mitch was my father.

23:41.129 --> 23:42.548
[SNIFFLES]

23:42.573 --> 23:44.580
[VOICE BREAKING] 'Cause
we're so different. I...

23:45.180 --> 23:47.901
We're so different, and I just... I...

23:49.737 --> 23:53.119
I-I blamed myself for
not being like him.

23:53.144 --> 23:56.010
And then I-I finally had an answer

23:56.035 --> 23:57.799
that explained everything.

23:57.824 --> 24:00.026
And... And I got to know them, and...

24:00.051 --> 24:02.010
And I liked them.

24:02.035 --> 24:03.885
And they liked me.

24:04.589 --> 24:07.588
Now I'm... I'm more alone than ever.

24:11.504 --> 24:14.166
You know what?
Let's talk about this downstairs.

24:14.191 --> 24:15.191
Come on, let's go...

24:15.216 --> 24:17.080
- Let's go downstairs.
- No. No! Stay back.

24:17.105 --> 24:19.151
It's... It's not fair!

24:19.176 --> 24:20.362
PJ.

24:20.598 --> 24:22.823
You are not alone.

24:22.848 --> 24:24.137
I am!

24:24.162 --> 24:25.994
- I-I am. I...
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]

24:26.559 --> 24:29.018
Let's just have a
glass of wine and talk.

24:29.043 --> 24:30.213
Yeah.

24:30.238 --> 24:32.940
Mitch. Barbara. What are you doing here?

24:32.965 --> 24:35.191
- [INDISTINCT TALKING]
- <i>PJ: I'm tired of trying to explain it.</i>

24:35.215 --> 24:36.385
- Rome?
- <i>You got to come down</i>

24:36.410 --> 24:37.776
<i>off of this roof, PJ.</i>

24:37.801 --> 24:39.135
<i>We are going to talk about it.</i>

24:39.167 --> 24:40.168
- Guys.
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]

24:40.192 --> 24:42.496
<i>I'm done talking!
Talking is what got me up here.</i>

24:42.521 --> 24:43.521
- Oh, my God.
- <i>PJ!</i>

24:43.546 --> 24:45.946
- <i>I don't think I can do this anymore.</i>
- They're on the roof.

24:46.549 --> 24:48.114
No, PJ, we can... We can talk to Maggie.

24:48.138 --> 24:49.809
W-What do you say we...
We come down from this roof

24:49.833 --> 24:50.833
and we talk to Maggie?

24:50.858 --> 24:53.308
I don't want to talk to Maggie.

24:53.333 --> 24:56.183
- <i>I don't want to talk to anyone.</i>
- Wait, wait, wait. Wait, wait, wait!

24:56.208 --> 24:57.787
- Wait! Stop, stop.
- What the hell are you doing?

24:57.811 --> 24:59.840
- Open the door!
- We can't go out there right now.

24:59.865 --> 25:01.638
What are you talking about?
My son is out there!

25:01.662 --> 25:03.474
I am a psychologist!
Rome is with him, and he trusts him.

25:03.498 --> 25:05.239
He is upset, but he doesn't want to die.

25:05.264 --> 25:06.598
We do not want to escalate this.

25:06.623 --> 25:09.426
<i>These last few weeks,
just spending time with you</i>

25:09.451 --> 25:12.239
and Sophie and Delilah, I...

25:13.582 --> 25:16.458
... I felt like I finally had a family.

25:16.483 --> 25:18.169
<i>I don't... I don't have that anymore.</i>

25:18.194 --> 25:20.647
Okay, look, PJ,
what does it mean to be family?

25:20.672 --> 25:21.709
Huh?

25:21.734 --> 25:23.990
You helped me bury my mom.

25:24.015 --> 25:25.553
<i>You stood right next to me</i>

25:25.578 --> 25:27.483
and Eddie and Gary and my brother

25:27.508 --> 25:29.764
because you are my family.

25:30.292 --> 25:32.647
Family's not just the
people who had you.

25:32.672 --> 25:34.467
Family's the people who...
who raise you,

25:34.492 --> 25:35.639
the people who love you.

25:35.664 --> 25:37.233
You don't think Mitch loves you?

25:37.258 --> 25:39.154
He lied to me my whole life!

25:39.608 --> 25:40.983
<i>You heard your mom.</i>

25:41.008 --> 25:42.717
<i>This guy wanted to be your dad.</i>

25:42.742 --> 25:43.912
<i>He stepped up.</i>

25:43.937 --> 25:45.819
<i>And he... he might not
show up in all the ways</i>

25:45.844 --> 25:47.217
that you want him to.

25:47.242 --> 25:49.061
Hell, neither does my dad.

25:49.086 --> 25:52.061
But these two men are our fathers!

25:52.086 --> 25:55.850
And they are trying to love
us the best way they can.

25:55.875 --> 25:58.037
And you know what? Sometimes... [SCOFFS]

25:58.066 --> 25:59.468
... we can be a little hard to love.

25:59.492 --> 26:02.397
No, it... it's just,
for as far back as I can remember,

26:02.422 --> 26:05.326
there's been this... this weight,

26:05.351 --> 26:07.873
and I didn't know why.

26:07.898 --> 26:10.467
<i>And then I found out a-about
Jon and his depression,</i>

26:10.492 --> 26:12.514
<i>and I thought I finally
figured out the reason.</i>

26:12.539 --> 26:15.444
I thought I finally figured
out why I feel this way.

26:15.469 --> 26:17.725
But I was wrong, and I don't, and I...

26:17.750 --> 26:20.162
God, no matter what I do, it's just...

26:20.187 --> 26:21.889
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

26:21.914 --> 26:23.725
- PJ!
- It's never gonna go away.

26:23.750 --> 26:24.764
PJ, don't!

26:24.789 --> 26:26.373
No, wait, wait, wait, wait! Wait, wait.

26:26.398 --> 26:27.475
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

26:27.500 --> 26:31.264
♪ Well, there's just an empty space ♪

26:33.005 --> 26:34.338
What are you doing?!

26:34.363 --> 26:35.623
Same thing you're doing.

26:35.648 --> 26:38.803
♪ Just the memory of your face ♪

26:38.828 --> 26:42.404
♪ Now take a look at me now ♪

26:42.429 --> 26:45.912
A year ago, I was right where you are.

26:45.937 --> 26:48.528
Wasn't a rooftop.
It was a mouthful of pills.

26:48.838 --> 26:50.826
Just like that script you read.

26:51.701 --> 26:54.647
Yes, man, there are some dark days!

26:54.874 --> 26:57.583
[VOICE BREAKING] But
there's also tomorrow.

26:57.608 --> 26:59.528
And I'm here for you!

27:01.387 --> 27:04.029
We are all here for you.

27:05.707 --> 27:07.858
<i>I will not lose you.</i>

27:07.883 --> 27:09.928
[CRYING]

27:09.953 --> 27:12.498
I will not lose you.

27:12.523 --> 27:16.233
♪ Take a good look at me now ♪

27:16.258 --> 27:20.490
♪ 'Cause I'll still be standing here ♪

27:20.627 --> 27:23.428
♪ And you coming back to me... ♪

27:23.453 --> 27:25.532
I got you.

27:26.546 --> 27:28.256
<i>I got you.</i>

27:35.632 --> 27:37.216
I got you.

27:38.247 --> 27:41.552
♪ Take a look at me now ♪

27:42.314 --> 27:44.646
Mm-hmm. Okay. Thanks, John.

27:44.671 --> 27:46.380
We're just glad you're safe.

27:47.003 --> 27:49.912
So, I got ahold of my
colleague Dr. Pratt.

27:49.937 --> 27:52.115
He's gonna meet you at admitting.

27:52.140 --> 27:53.943
All he's gonna do is talk to you

27:53.968 --> 27:56.912
and decide whether or not
you have to stay the night.

27:57.089 --> 27:59.128
We're gonna get you the help you need.

27:59.270 --> 28:00.701
Thank you.

28:02.358 --> 28:03.935
It's okay.

28:03.960 --> 28:05.615
[INHALES SHARPLY]

28:05.640 --> 28:07.059
He's okay.

28:14.077 --> 28:15.717
BARBARA: I was just
trying to protect you.

28:15.741 --> 28:17.091
[VOICE BREAKING] I'm sorry.

28:17.116 --> 28:18.904
I should've told you.

28:21.388 --> 28:23.130
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:28.981 --> 28:30.060
D.

28:30.155 --> 28:31.810
What are you doing here?

28:31.835 --> 28:34.068
Here's the form you wanted.
I-I signed it.

28:34.093 --> 28:36.177
It says that you're Charlie's father.

28:36.507 --> 28:37.836
Katherine, maybe...

28:37.861 --> 28:40.191
Maybe you can file it in the morning.

28:43.170 --> 28:44.646
Thank you.

28:46.177 --> 28:48.177
W-We're doing the right thing.

28:48.202 --> 28:50.537
I know, just...

28:50.729 --> 28:52.490
I don't know how I'm gonna handle it

28:52.515 --> 28:54.412
if they don't take it well.

28:54.746 --> 28:57.021
We'll handle it the way Gary said.

28:57.404 --> 28:59.162
As a family.

28:59.187 --> 29:02.826
♪♪

29:02.851 --> 29:04.022
- [COLIN GRUNTS]
- GARY: Let's go.

29:04.046 --> 29:05.771
Get up there.

29:05.997 --> 29:08.115
- MAGGIE: Mm.
- [SIGHS] Hey.

29:08.140 --> 29:09.646
[COLIN PANTING]

29:09.671 --> 29:11.091
How's the kid? Is he okay?

29:11.116 --> 29:12.825
Mm. Yeah.

29:12.850 --> 29:14.771
I mean, he will be.
He's been through a lot.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.295
How's Rome?

29:16.320 --> 29:17.649
Mm.

29:17.674 --> 29:19.633
He was incredible.

29:19.658 --> 29:21.763
Good. [SNIFFS]

29:21.788 --> 29:23.506
- I see you found your passport.
- [CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

29:23.530 --> 29:24.772
I was starting to think
you weren't a citizen.

29:24.796 --> 29:26.616
I had a whole birther
thing going on in my head.

29:26.640 --> 29:27.904
[CHUCKLES]

29:27.929 --> 29:29.795
Hey, uh, listen.

29:29.811 --> 29:31.680
After everything that's happened today,

29:31.681 --> 29:34.521
I feel like you and I
should talk about stuff.

29:37.405 --> 29:38.824
Yeah.

29:39.207 --> 29:41.302
Absolutely. Uh...

29:42.437 --> 29:45.146
I'm sorry I didn't
tell you about my job.

29:45.271 --> 29:46.959
But I'll get another one.

29:46.984 --> 29:48.693
Maybe in England.

29:49.057 --> 29:50.420
Um...

29:50.445 --> 29:53.774
Gary, when I... found my passport,

29:53.799 --> 29:57.279
um, I also found this.

29:57.775 --> 29:59.099
Whoa!

29:59.124 --> 30:00.154
In the...

30:00.179 --> 30:02.154
[LAUGHS] No. No, no, no, Maggie.

30:02.179 --> 30:03.928
Uh... [CLEARS THROAT]

30:03.953 --> 30:06.122
This, uh, I got for you...

30:06.147 --> 30:09.084
[SIGHS] ... when you were sick.

30:09.109 --> 30:10.810
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

30:10.835 --> 30:12.295
And I wasn't sure if you were...

30:15.942 --> 30:17.651
You know.

30:17.676 --> 30:20.912
No. No, no. This... This is from before.

30:20.937 --> 30:22.646
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

30:22.671 --> 30:24.482
- Whew! [CHUCKLES]
- Yeah.

30:26.628 --> 30:28.732
[SIGHS, CHUCKLES]

30:28.757 --> 30:30.257
[CHUCKLES]

30:32.536 --> 30:34.099
Wow.

30:34.124 --> 30:35.209
No, it's just...

30:35.234 --> 30:37.281
- It's just a lot. I mean...
- It's just that you thought

30:37.305 --> 30:38.812
I was gonna propose.

30:38.837 --> 30:40.327
And...

30:40.589 --> 30:41.958
that was your reaction.

30:41.983 --> 30:43.976
Gary, we've known each other
less than a year.

30:44.001 --> 30:45.921
[LAUGHING] That would be crazy.

30:48.048 --> 30:49.178
Would it?

30:50.453 --> 30:52.554
I mean, a little bit, right?

30:53.200 --> 30:54.874
[CHUCKLES]

30:54.899 --> 30:56.952
- What?
- Um...

31:00.652 --> 31:02.460
When you were sick,

31:02.739 --> 31:04.210
we had this...

31:06.074 --> 31:07.569
... this way.

31:09.892 --> 31:11.891
And now I feel, um...

31:17.494 --> 31:19.258
Let me ask you something.

31:19.283 --> 31:21.242
When you were lying
in that hospital bed,

31:21.267 --> 31:22.867
when you looked at me and you told me

31:22.892 --> 31:25.642
that you wanted to spend the
rest of your life with me...

31:28.405 --> 31:30.211
... did you say that because...

31:30.740 --> 31:34.289
you thought the rest of your life
was only gonna be six months?

31:41.872 --> 31:44.469
[SIGHS]

31:44.726 --> 31:46.685
[VOICE BREAKING] I don't know.

31:53.397 --> 31:55.038
- Oh, my God.
- Gary, you said it yourself.

31:55.062 --> 31:56.460
You got that for me when I was sick.

31:56.484 --> 31:58.162
I'm not sick anymore.

31:58.312 --> 32:00.311
Things have changed.

32:00.336 --> 32:01.835
Yeah, but not for me they haven't.

32:01.860 --> 32:03.201
Well, that's the problem.

32:03.226 --> 32:05.052
You're acting like I still have cancer,

32:05.077 --> 32:07.927
like you have to drop
everything to save me.

32:07.952 --> 32:09.521
But I'm... I'm not there anymore.

32:09.546 --> 32:11.896
You gave me a post-it
that said "I'm in."

32:11.921 --> 32:13.840
And apparently, you didn't mean that.

32:13.865 --> 32:14.974
That's not fair.

32:14.999 --> 32:16.256
No, what's not fair is that I...

32:16.280 --> 32:18.701
I would give you this right
now if I thought you wanted it.

32:18.726 --> 32:19.895
But you don't.

32:19.920 --> 32:21.849
Gary, you gave me a life

32:21.874 --> 32:24.388
that I didn't even
think I was gonna have.

32:24.413 --> 32:27.122
I'm not saying that I don't
want to spend it with you.

32:27.147 --> 32:29.279
I am saying I don't know what it is yet.

32:29.304 --> 32:30.818
It's this!

32:30.843 --> 32:31.962
It's all of this!

32:31.987 --> 32:34.748
It's me, willing to give you everything!

32:34.773 --> 32:37.380
- I'm in love with you!
- And I'm in love with you!

32:37.405 --> 32:39.599
But before I can say
that I can be half of us,

32:39.624 --> 32:41.826
I have to figure out what my half is.

32:41.830 --> 32:44.564
And I'm not saying this
to hurt you. I'm not.

32:44.589 --> 32:45.918
That's the last thing I want.

32:45.943 --> 32:47.442
But I know

32:47.443 --> 32:50.662
that between losing Jon and your mom,

32:50.687 --> 32:52.100
- you have a lot of prob...
- Stop it. No, stop.

32:52.124 --> 32:53.849
You don't get to do that. No, no.

32:53.874 --> 32:54.951
And not in a conversation

32:54.976 --> 32:56.975
where you are not
willing to commit to me,

32:57.000 --> 32:58.615
you don't get to bring up my mother.

32:58.818 --> 33:00.237
This is about you and me

33:00.262 --> 33:03.141
and you not willing to commit.

33:03.166 --> 33:10.166
♪♪

33:10.191 --> 33:13.417
You keep saying that you need to
know who you are without cancer.

33:14.224 --> 33:15.620
I get it.

33:16.798 --> 33:17.837
[SIGHS]

33:17.862 --> 33:19.534
While you're doing that...

33:20.456 --> 33:23.285
maybe I need to figure
out who I am without you.

33:35.842 --> 33:37.425
Is that really what you want?

33:37.465 --> 33:40.378
- You want us to end this?
- No.

33:40.403 --> 33:44.675
What I want is for you to want us

33:44.700 --> 33:46.610
the way you used to.

33:47.841 --> 33:49.471
But you don't.

33:53.158 --> 33:54.407
So go.

33:54.899 --> 33:59.198
♪♪

33:59.223 --> 34:00.753
[SIGHS]

34:00.778 --> 34:02.027
[CRYING]

34:02.052 --> 34:03.635
[SNIFFLES]

34:14.855 --> 34:17.699
Your dad and I met at Ground Zero.

34:18.245 --> 34:20.972
MITCH: She had lost Dave, and...

34:20.996 --> 34:23.120
I'd lost my whole battalion.

34:23.145 --> 34:24.558
[GOO GOO DOLLS' "IRIS" PLAYS]

34:24.583 --> 34:26.058
[SNIFFLES]

34:26.083 --> 34:29.121
[VOICE BREAKING] We had both lost
what was most important to us.

34:29.458 --> 34:32.456
And somehow, despite it all...

34:32.482 --> 34:34.942
Or maybe because of it all...

34:36.766 --> 34:38.558
... we fell in love.

34:40.596 --> 34:43.105
Dad wanted to raise you as his own.

34:43.130 --> 34:44.659
He wanted to adopt you.

34:44.960 --> 34:47.214
I wanted us to be a family.

34:47.239 --> 34:51.868
♪ And I'd give up forever to touch you ♪

34:51.893 --> 34:56.058
♪ 'Cause I know that
you feel me somehow ♪

34:56.083 --> 35:00.933
♪ You're the closest to
Heaven that I'll ever be ♪

35:00.958 --> 35:04.995
♪ And I don't want to
go home right now ♪

35:05.020 --> 35:06.469
What's going on?

35:06.494 --> 35:10.511
♪♪

35:10.536 --> 35:11.906
What is it?

35:13.364 --> 35:16.886
There's something we need
to talk about as a family.

35:16.911 --> 35:18.620
Is this about Dad?

35:18.784 --> 35:20.441
It's... It's about Charlie.

35:20.466 --> 35:21.785
And me.

35:23.277 --> 35:28.066
♪ And I don't want the world to see me ♪

35:28.091 --> 35:32.785
♪ 'Cause I don't think
that they'd understand ♪

35:32.810 --> 35:37.066
♪ When everything's made to be broken ♪

35:37.091 --> 35:41.988
♪ I just want you to know who I am ♪

35:42.013 --> 35:45.284
♪♪

35:45.309 --> 35:46.809
Gina.

35:47.901 --> 35:50.245
Everything that I have
put you through today

35:50.270 --> 35:52.066
must have been hard to
see, but I am not...

35:52.091 --> 35:55.753
I am so proud of you, babe.

35:58.285 --> 36:00.753
I almost lost you eight months ago.

36:01.807 --> 36:03.261
But today...

36:03.579 --> 36:06.026
you were strong,

36:06.051 --> 36:08.276
confident,

36:08.301 --> 36:09.495
unafraid.

36:09.520 --> 36:10.675
I don't know about unafraid.

36:10.700 --> 36:12.894
Oh, I do. You were willing...

36:12.919 --> 36:15.823
You were willing to risk
your life to save PJ's.

36:16.397 --> 36:19.089
The way you were with him
today, that's...

36:21.117 --> 36:23.097
... what a parent should do.

36:23.122 --> 36:26.628
♪♪

36:26.653 --> 36:31.237
Part of the reason I wasn't
sure I could be a mom

36:31.262 --> 36:33.503
was because I didn't
have that growing up.

36:34.171 --> 36:35.433
But I look at you and your mom,

36:35.458 --> 36:37.972
and I realize what a great job she did.

36:40.913 --> 36:42.872
And I want to do that for someone.

36:42.897 --> 36:47.306
♪♪

36:47.331 --> 36:49.040
Are you... Are you s-saying...

36:49.065 --> 36:51.901
I'm saying I want to adopt a baby.

36:53.669 --> 36:55.998
I want to save someone, too.

36:56.023 --> 36:57.698
[LAUGHS]

36:57.723 --> 37:02.097
♪♪

37:02.122 --> 37:05.121
[TAPE RIPPING]

37:19.166 --> 37:23.808
♪ And I don't want the world to see me ♪

37:23.833 --> 37:27.933
♪ 'Cause I don't think
that they'd understand ♪

37:27.958 --> 37:28.958
[KEYS JINGLE]

37:28.983 --> 37:32.566
♪ When everything's made to be broken ♪

37:32.591 --> 37:37.433
♪ I just want you to know who I am ♪

37:40.121 --> 37:42.120
[SOBBING]

37:54.920 --> 37:56.225
Hey, pal.

38:00.396 --> 38:02.694
There's something we want
to talk to you about.

38:02.859 --> 38:04.257
[THUD]

38:04.481 --> 38:05.772
What was that?

38:05.797 --> 38:06.916
[THUD]

38:07.363 --> 38:08.749
I don't know.

38:09.702 --> 38:13.827
♪ And you can't fight the
tears that ain't comin' ♪

38:14.112 --> 38:18.428
♪ Or the moment of truth in your lies ♪

38:18.734 --> 38:20.702
MAGGIE: No, I understand.

38:20.727 --> 38:22.108
[INHALES DEEPLY]

38:22.133 --> 38:25.319
Yeah. I would love to be
considered in the future.

38:26.328 --> 38:28.546
Thanks for letting me know.

38:30.336 --> 38:34.007
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]
- That was Oxford.

38:35.087 --> 38:36.897
I didn't get the fellowship.

38:37.262 --> 38:39.632
Oh, Maggie. I'm so sorry.

38:40.391 --> 38:41.897
Me too.

38:41.922 --> 38:45.850
♪ When everything
feels like the movies ♪

38:46.007 --> 38:48.014
- ♪ Yeah, you bleed ♪
- After you.

38:48.055 --> 38:50.382
♪ Just to know you're alive ♪

38:53.254 --> 38:54.999
Thanks for doing this.

38:55.389 --> 38:56.803
I didn't know who else to call.

38:56.828 --> 38:59.475
You know, 'cause
everyone else I know in town,

38:59.500 --> 39:02.132
I know through... Gary,

39:02.157 --> 39:04.749
and I'm not ready to tell them yet.

39:05.082 --> 39:06.758
Just in case...

39:09.868 --> 39:11.524
[SIGHS]

39:12.587 --> 39:13.688
I'm just not ready.

39:13.713 --> 39:16.540
Yeah. I get it.

39:17.594 --> 39:18.724
[CLEARS THROAT]

39:23.430 --> 39:24.946
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

39:25.390 --> 39:27.219
Hey. What's up, buddy?

39:27.244 --> 39:29.688
Yeah, I'm...
I'm helping her move right now.

39:30.615 --> 39:31.993
[SIGHS]

39:32.018 --> 39:33.307
I'm gonna tell her.

39:33.332 --> 39:36.032
Now is just... not the right time.

39:41.020 --> 39:42.309
Okay.

39:53.590 --> 39:54.897
[THUD]

39:55.270 --> 39:56.694
[WOMAN GRUNTING]

39:57.734 --> 39:59.653
[THUD]

39:59.678 --> 40:02.093
- [WOMAN SHOUTS]
- [THUD]

40:02.118 --> 40:03.178
[THUD]

40:03.187 --> 40:06.082
You spoke at his funeral!

40:06.107 --> 40:07.566
You were his friend!

40:07.567 --> 40:08.780
[GRUNTS]

40:08.805 --> 40:10.424
I trusted you!

40:10.449 --> 40:14.428
♪ And I don't want the world to see me ♪

40:15.645 --> 40:18.038
- I am so sorry.
- Don't.

40:19.496 --> 40:22.653
♪ When everything's made to be broken ♪

40:22.678 --> 40:24.057
[VOICE BREAKING] I hate you.

40:24.082 --> 40:28.288
♪ I just want you to know who I am ♪

40:28.313 --> 40:32.913
- ♪ I just want you to know who I am ♪
- [SOPHIE YELLS]

